Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Peel and dice the
@Russet Potato{2}(peeled and diced) into ½-inch cubes. Place in a #medium pot{} with
a large pinch of @salt{pinch} and enough water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a
boil, then reduce to a simmer for ~{10-12%minutes}, until fork-tender. Drain and
return to the same #pot{}.

== Broccolini ==

Roast the broccolini: Toss the @baby broccoli{6%oz} on a #baking sheet{} with a
drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.
Place in the oven for about ~{15%minutes}, tossing halfway through cooking, until
golden brown.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced).
Strip the @rosemary{1/4%oz} from the sprig and roughly chop the leaves.

== Pork ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Season the @boneless pork chops{12%oz} on all sides with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Add the pork to the pan and cook for ~{2-3%minutes} per side, until browned but
not yet cooked to desired doneness. Transfer to the baking sheet in the oven to
finish cooking for ~{5-7%minutes}. Remove from the oven to rest for ~{5%minutes}
before thinly slicing.

== Onion Gravy ==

Meanwhile, heat another drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in the same #pan{} over
medium heat. Add the onions and half the rosemary to the pan and cook, tossing
for ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened. Add the @butter{1%tbsp} to the pan and stir
to melt. Sprinkle the @flour{1%tbsp} over the onions while they cook, tossing
for ~{1%minute}. Whisk ½ cup water and the @chicken stock concentrate{1} into the
pan. Bring to a boil, then simmer on low heat until thickened, for ~{2-3%minutes}.
Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Rosemary Mashed Potatoes ==

Meanwhile, reheat the potatoes in the pot over medium heat. Add @milk{1/4%cup} and
the remaining rosemary, then mash with a #fork{} or #potato masher{} until smooth.
Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Serve the pan seared pork chops on a bed of rosemary mashed potatoes, with the
broccolini to the side. Drizzle the onion gravy over top. Enjoy!